If you infer mean, median, … from population itʼs called parameter.

Similarly, if you infer mean, median, … from sample itʼs called statistic or estimate.




Type 1 Error ( False Positive )


Type I error = Reject H0 when H0 is true.

Type I error is denoted by α (alpha), which is also known as the significance level.







 
Type 2 Error ( False Negative ) 


Type II error = Fail to reject H0 when H0 is false.


Type II error is denoted by β (beta)











